choices.text: For the second experiment, Sara used 4 test tubes (since she had already used 2 in the first experiment). For the third experiment, she also used 4 test tubes since it required the same number as the second experiment. Therefore, a total of 8 + 4 + 4 = 16 test tubes were needed for all three experiments combined.
